HEADWORD: Quotha
<hw>Quoth"a</hw> <pr>(kw⟦omac⟧th"⟦adot⟧)</pr>, <pos>interj.</pos>
<ety>[For <ets>quoth 'a</ets>, said he, <ets>'a</ets> being corrupted
from <ets>he</ets>.]</ety> <def>Indeed; forsooth.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To affront the blessed hillside drabs and thieves⟦br⟧
With mended morals, <qex>quotha</qex>, -- fine new lives !</q>
<rj><qau>Mrs. Browning.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

